Text:
(I've been busy running all over the place, taking
out villains trying to uncover the secret of my
money... I mean, the counterfeit money.)

(But just for today, working solo and putting in
extra hours doesn't bother me one bit.)

(Besides, Yukime said she wasn't in it for the
money...)
(Which means I can keep all of it for myself!)

(Yukime should be back soon. All I have to do now is
gaze down on the city from somewhere up high.)
(murmur something cryptic, and my work here is done.)
The crisis has begun. All according to plan...

(My patrols were perfect. Not even a mouse could
have made it here from the Lawless City...)
It's Lady Yukime—we've lost contact with her!

Moving a hefty amount of gold coins would take time.
Unless they're incredibly efficient, they couldn't
have gone far—
Do you two know where he is?

Gettan... You dared to touch something very
important to me...

The ground is piled high with pristine snow. 
The pearly moon gleams overhead, accompanied by
a host of stars.

With the beautiful black-and-white night as a
backdrop, blade and fans meet.
Golden fur...nine tails... So the legends are true...

If I had that kind of power...I wouldn’t have
everything taken from me—!
Will you now use that power just to take from me?!
Not yet! If only had the money you stole—!
I can still get it all back!
If I had money...if I had power—!

I don't know what it is that made you this way.
But, although you murdered my mother...

The fact that you once saved my village and my life
remains unchanged...

Sins do not erase good deeds, nor do good deeds
erase sins.

I choose to believe that the Gettan who saved me that
day still resides somewhere inside you...

Yukime turns and begins walking away across the
snowy plain.
He pops a red pill into his mouth.
A flower of blood blooms atop the snow.
A memory flashes across Gettan's mind.
The only way to protect what's yours...
